## 📂 Project Structure

```text
src/
├── data/           # Unified data processing and DataLoader generation
├── models/         # Student, Teacher, and Uncertainty fusion architectures
├── core/           # Standardized Training, Evaluation, and Trainer logic
├── utils/          # Config management, hybrid metrics, and seeding
└── main.py         # Primary entry point
configs/            # Experiment-specific YAML configurations
data/               # Storage for raw and processed datasets
output/             # Experiment results, checkpoints, and logs
```

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1. Installation
This project requires [uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) for dependency management.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-repo/UGTS-DTI.git
cd UGTS-DTI
make install
```

### 2. Running High-Quality Checks
Keep the codebase clean with `ruff` and `mypy` (pre-configured to `pvrptw` standards):

```bash
make check   # Run linting + type checking
make format  # Automatically fix formatting issues
```

### 3. Usage
Configure your experiment in `configs/default.yaml` and run:

```bash
# Execute training with default settings
uv run python -m src.main

# Overwrite with custom configuration
uv run python -m src.main --config configs/your_config.yaml
```

---

## 📊 Evaluation Metrics
UGTS-DTI implements a comprehensive set of DTI-specific metrics:

| Perspective | Metrics |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Traditional DTI** | AUPRC, AUROC |
| **Regression-style** | Concordance Index (CI), MSE, RMSE, Pearson Correlation |
| **Classification** | Accuracy, F1, Precision, Recall, Specificity |

